[[!meta title="Reading and writing emails with Icedove (Thunderbird)"]]

For reading and writing email, Tails includes <span
class="application">Icedove</span>, also known as <span class="application">[Thunderbird](https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/)</span>.

<div class="tip">
<p><span class="application">Icedove</span> is the name of <span
class="application">Thunderbird</span> in Tails and they are otherwise the same
program.</p>
</div>

To start <span class="application">Icedove</span> choose
<span class="menuchoice">
  <span class="guimenu">Applications</span>&nbsp;▸
  <span class="guisubmenu">Internet</span>&nbsp;▸
  <span class="guimenuitem">Icedove</span></span>.

OpenPGP encryption with Enigmail
================================

<span class="application">Icedove in Tails includes the
<span class="application">[Enigmail](https://www.enigmail.net/)</span>
extension to encrypt and authenticate emails using OpenPGP.
